# Commit Types:
# feat     - new feature or logic
# fix      - bug fix or correction
# chore    - non-functional change (e.g. formatting, cleanup)
# docs     - documentation only
# refactor - code restructure without behavior change
# perf     - performance improvement
# test     - adding or updating tests

# Scopes:
# sql         - query monitoring, filter validation, schema changes
# auth        - role hygiene, user indexing
# storage     - object ID generation
# connection  - connection strategy and pooler setup
# onboarding  - folder structure, README, contributor guidance

# Examples:
# feat(sql): implement subscription filter validation trigger
# docs(auth): document password reset hygiene for supabase roles
# fix(storage): set gen_random_uuid() default for object IDs
# chore(connection): update session pooler notes for IPv4 fallback
# docs(onboarding): scaffold README with validation steps and folder map

# Notes:
